# Kubernetes NodePort Service

A **NodePort Service** is used to expose an application running inside a Kubernetes cluster to external users.

When a service is created with type **NodePort**, Kubernetes opens a specific port on every worker node. External users can access the application using the **Node IP address and NodePort**.

Traffic Flow

```
User → Node Public IP : NodePort → Service → Pod → Container
```

Example NodePort Service Manifest

```yaml
apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: javawebappsvc

spec:
  type: NodePort

  selector:
    app: javawebapp

  ports:
  - port: 80
    targetPort: 8080
```

In this configuration:

| Field | Meaning |
|------|--------|
| port | Service port |
| targetPort | Container port |
| type | Service type (NodePort) |

---

# What is NodePort Number?

When we do not specify a `nodePort` value in the service YAML file, Kubernetes automatically assigns a **random port**.

Default NodePort range:

```
30000 - 32767
```

Example:

```
NodePort automatically assigned → 30045
```

You can check it using:

```bash
kubectl get service
```

---

# Specify Custom NodePort

If you want to define a specific NodePort number, you can add the **nodePort field**.

Example:

```yaml
apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: javawebappsvc

spec:
  type: NodePort

  selector:
    app: javawebapp

  ports:
  - port: 80
    targetPort: 8080
    nodePort: 30070
```

Now the application will be accessible using:

```
NodePort → 30070
```

---

# Deploy NodePort Service

Apply manifest file

```bash
kubectl apply -f service.yaml
```

Check pods

```bash
kubectl get pods
```

Check services

```bash
kubectl get service
```

Check pod node details

```bash
kubectl get pods -o wide
```

---

# Important AWS / Cloud Configuration

If you are running Kubernetes on **AWS EC2 worker nodes**, you must allow the NodePort in the **Security Group inbound rules**.

Example rule

```
Type : Custom TCP
Port : 30070
Source : 0.0.0.0/0
```

---

# Access Application Using NodePort

Application URL format

```
http://node-public-ip:node-port/java-web-app
```

Example

```
http://3.110.25.120:30070/java-web-app
```

